00022 //
00023 // Define the "special" processor bus used by all machines that run a
00024 // DECchip 21264.  The processor bus is used to access the internal
00025 // performance counters.
00026 //
00027 
00028 #define PROCESSOR_BUS_21264 21264
00029 
00030 //
00031 // Define the physical address bit that turns on user-mode access
00032 // to I/O space in the pfn of a pte.  This bit is required because of
00033 // the current 36 bit physical address space limit on NT.
00034 //
00035 
00036 #define EV6_USER_IO_ADDRESS_SPACE (ULONGLONG)(0x800000000)
